children.subject: Both are great, shouldn't matter. I find Sergey really boring as a lecturer, but 188 notes are great.
Sorry, what do you mean by group linde up?
For 162, it should really depend on whether or not you have a group lined up beforehand.

history.content:
I am planning to take CS188 or CS 162 this coming Fall 19. Since I am taking other two other technicals classes and probably one one-unit, non-technical class, so I need to push one or the other to next year. I do understand that each professor's philosophy and approaches are different, but I would love to hear which combo would you recommend based on your experiences:

Combo 1:

Fall 2019: CS188 by Anca Dragan

Spring 2020: C162 by John D. Kubiatowicz

Combo 2:

Fall 2019: C162 by David E. Culler

Spring 2020: CS188 by Sergey Levine

Thank you!
